mainText: A SQL injection vulnerability in SourceCodester Online Shopping Alphaware 1.0 allows remote unauthenticated attackers to bypass the authentication process via email and password parameters. This is CVE-2020-24208 published on August 17 2020

ShopXO v1.8.1 has a command execution vulnerability. Attackers can use this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands and gain control of the server. This is CVE-2020-24220 published on August 17 2020
ldebug.c in Lua 5.4.0 attempts to access debug information via the line hook of a stripped function, leading to a NULL pointer dereference. This is CVE-2020-24369 published on August 17 2020
ldebug.c in Lua 5.4.0 allows a negation overflow and segmentation fault in getlocal and setlocal, as demonstrated by getlocal(3,2^31). This is CVE-2020-24370 published on August 17 2020
lgc.c in Lua 5.4.0 mishandles the interaction between barriers and the sweep phase, leading to a memory access violation involving collectgarbage. This is CVE-2020-24371 published on August 17 2020
